{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.1",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 1 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:1",
      "text": "The proverbs of Solomon, the son of David, king of Israel:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:2",
      "text": "to know wisdom and instruction; to discern the words of understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:3",
      "text": "to receive instruction in wise dealing, in righteousness, justice, and equity;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:4",
      "text": "to give prudence to the simple, knowledge and discretion to the young man —",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:5",
      "text": "that the wise man may hear, and increase in learning; that the man of understanding may attain to sound counsel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:6",
      "text": "to understand a proverb and parables, the words and riddles of the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:7",
      "text": "The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of knowledge, but the foolish despise wisdom and instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:8",
      "text": "My son, listen to your father’s instruction, and don’t forsake your mother’s teaching;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:9",
      "text": "for they will be a garland to grace your head, and chains around your neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:10",
      "text": "My son, if sinners entice you, don’t consent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:11",
      "text": "If they say, “Come with us. Let’s lie in wait for blood. Let’s lurk secretly for the innocent without cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:12",
      "text": "Let’s swallow them up alive like Sheol, and whole, like those who go down into the pit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:13",
      "text": "We’ll find all valuable wealth. We’ll fill our houses with plunder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:14",
      "text": "You shall cast your lot among us. We’ll all have one purse”—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:15",
      "text": "my son, don’t walk on the path with them. Keep your foot from their path,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:16",
      "text": "for their feet run to evil. They hurry to shed blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:17",
      "text": "For the net is spread in vain in the sight of any bird;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:18",
      "text": "but these lay in wait for their own blood. They lurk secretly for their own lives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:19",
      "text": "So are the ways of everyone who is greedy for gain. It takes away the life of its owners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:20",
      "text": "Wisdom calls aloud in the street. She utters her voice in the public squares.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:21",
      "text": "She calls at the head of noisy places. At the entrance of the city gates, she utters her words:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:22",
      "text": "“How long, you simple ones, will you love simplicity? How long will mockers delight themselves in mockery, and fools hate knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:23",
      "text": "Turn at my reproof. Behold, I will pour out my spirit on you. I will make known my words to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:24",
      "text": "Because I have called, and you have refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no one has paid attention;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:25",
      "text": "but you have ignored all my counsel, and wanted none of my reproof;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:26",
      "text": "I also will laugh at your disaster. I will mock when calamity overtakes you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:27",
      "text": "when calamity overtakes you like a storm, when your disaster comes on like a whirlwind, when distress and anguish come on you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:28",
      "text": "Then they will call on me, but I will not answer. They will seek me diligently, but they will not find me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:29",
      "text": "because they hated knowledge, and didn’t choose the fear of Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:30",
      "text": "They wanted none of my counsel. They despised all my reproof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:31",
      "text": "Therefore they will eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own schemes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:32",
      "text": "For the backsliding of the simple will kill them. The careless ease of fools will destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.1.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:33",
      "text": "But whoever listens to me will dwell securely, and will be at ease, without fear of harm.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
